{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JvVpRwaipQMs5zDEDutac2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me create the `CloseCallRoundPage.tsx`. The API response for closecall rounds from `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:roundId` has these fields:\n\n```\npda, game: \"closecall\", phase, matchId, openPrice, openPriceExpo, greenPool, redPool, totalPool, \ngreenEntries (array), redEntries (array), greenCount, redCount, createdAt,\n// if settled:\nclosePrice, outcome, totalFee, settleTx, settledAt, verification\n```\n\nThe entries arrays contain objects like `{player, amountLamports}`.\n\n\nI need to set up the page component following the LordRoundPage pattern, add the routing for both the deep-link and proof pages, and update the history modal to point to the proof page.\n\nActually, looking at the spec more carefully — the route should be `/close-call/:roundId` for the main page, and I need to check if there's a separate proof page needed or if it's all on one page like the other games.\n\nSince Close Call uses oracle data rather than commit-reveal, I don't need the same verification flow. Let me build the component following the LordRoundPage pattern but adapted for the oracle-based settlement data — displaying the open price, pools, entries, and settlement details all in one view.\n\nFor the route, the spec is clear: `/close-call/:roundId` as a standalone round details page, not a proof variant. I'll link from the history modal directly to this route.\n\nWriting the component...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2713,"cache_read_input_tokens":71315,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2713},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"89d4f6ce-bf36-41